subject: Re: Quality with a K
msgSnippet: Page 14 of the manual talks about using just the lower half of Way in words like word , work and wild . So I often use the lower half of Way , hanging
messageBody:
Page 14 of the manual talks about using just the lower half of "Way" in words like "word", "work" and "wild". So I often use the lower half of "Way", hanging off the bottom of "Key", to represent "kw" or "qu". I write it in one go, top to bottom.  In notes, I often use this "Key + half Way" character as an abbreviation for the word "question".

Non-standard, and I'm sure there's a purist out there who will object, but no-one else has to read my writing.

Cheers,

Anthony
